# Frontend — React / Next.js

Activate when editing React or Next.js UI code.

## Components

- Prefer small, focused components; use `handle*` for event handlers; extract hooks or subcomponents when complexity grows.

## State

- Avoid unnecessary `useEffect`; prefer derived state; keep local state minimal.

## Next.js (App Router)

- Prefer Server Components by default; mark `"use client"` only when needed; keep secrets and sensitive env on the server.

## UI quality

- Design loading, error, empty, and disabled states; preserve accessibility (semantics, labels, keyboard, focus).

## Styling

- Prefer Tailwind when the project uses it.
